<div class="container mt-3">
  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-body">

      <h2 class="card-title mb-4">Privacy Policy</h2>

      <h4 class="card-subtitle mb-3">1. Introduction:</h4>
      <p class="card-text">Welcome to Wanderlust! This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect the information you provide when using our platform to host your home and make it available to users.</p>

      <h4 class="card-subtitle mb-3">2. Information We Collect:</h4>
      <p class="card-text">We collect various types of information to facilitate the hosting process, including but not limited to:</p>
      <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item">Personal Information: Name, contact information, profile picture.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Property Information: Details about your home, amenities, and location.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Transaction Information: Payment details for hosting transactions.</li>
      </ul>

      <h4 class="card-subtitle mt-2 mb-3">3. How Information is Collected:</h4>
      <p class="card-text">We collect information through the Airbnb platform, including user profiles, hosting forms, messaging, and transaction details. We may also collect information through cookies and similar technologies.</p>

      <h4 class="card-subtitle mb-3">4. Purpose of Collection:</h4>
      <p class="card-text">We collect information for the purpose of:</p>
      <ul class="list-group">
        <li class="list-group-item">Facilitating bookings and transactions.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Enhancing user experience.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Providing customer support.</li>
        <li class="list-group-item">Complying with legal requirements.</li>
      </ul>

      <h4 class="card-subtitle mb-3">5. Use of Cookies:</h4>
      <p class="card-text">We use cookies and similar technologies to improve the functionality of our platform, personalize content, and analyze usage patterns. Users can manage cookie preferences through their browser settings.</p>

      <h4 class="card-subtitle mb-3">6. Third-Party Services:</h4>
      <p class="card-text">We may use third-party services for analytics, payment processing, and other purposes. These services may collect and process user data in accordance with their own privacy policies.</p>

      <h4 class="card-subtitle mb-3">7. Data Security:</h4>
      <p class="card-text">We employ security measures to protect user data from unauthorized access, disclosure, or alteration. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is entirely secure.</p>

      <h4 class="card-subtitle mb-3">8. User Rights:</h4>
      <p class="card-text">Users have the right to access, correct, or delete their personal information. They can manage their privacy settings through their Airbnb account.</p>

      <h4 class="card-subtitle mb-3">9. Data Retention:</h4>
      <p class="card-text">We retain user data for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this privacy policy. Users can request data deletion in accordance with applicable laws.</p>

      <h4 class="card-subtitle mb-3">10. Policy Changes:</h4>
      <p class="card-text">We may update this privacy policy to reflect changes in our practices. Users will be notified of any significant changes, and continued use of our platform constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>

      <h4 class="card-subtitle mb-3">11. Contact Information:</h4>
      <p class="card-text">For privacy-related inquiries or concerns, please contact us at <a href="mailto:airbnb@gmail.com">airbnb@gmail.com</a></p>

      <h4 class="card-subtitle mb-3">12. Legal Compliance:</h4>
      <p class="card-text">This privacy policy complies with relevant privacy laws and regulations</p>

      <p class="card-text"><small class="text-muted">Date of Last Update: 29/09/2021</small></p>

    </div>
